        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 2 at 5:38PM EDT by NWS Detroit/Pontiac MI</headline>
        <description>At 537 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a cluster of strong
thunderstorms over Beecher back to Marion Springs, moving southeast
at 35 mph.

HAZARD...Winds in excess of 40 mph and half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Flint, Flushing, Davison, Clio, Chesaning, St. Charles, New Lothrop,
Burton, Mount Morris, Montrose, Oakley, Beecher, Marion Springs,
Crossroads Village, Genesee, Nelson, Brant, Burt, Layton Corners, and
Thetford Township.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
